unittitle.value: Brooklyn Historical Society mixed ephemera collection

abstract.value: This collection contains pamphlets, brochures, playbills, catalogs, programs and other materials dating from 1783 to 1994 and relating to a range of individuals, families, and institutions from Brooklyn, Long Island and the Hudson Valley region. The collection was compiled by library staff at the Brooklyn Historical Society.

p.value: Identification of item, date (if known); Brooklyn Historical Society mixed ephemera collection, ARC.314, Box and Folder number; Brooklyn Historical Society.
Immediate source of acquisition unknown. This collection was artifically compiled by Brooklyn Historical Society staff.

This collection was compiled by Brooklyn Historical Society staff. These materials were previously part of the BHS vertical files collection, but were physcially removed from vertical files at an unknown date.

This collection consists of materials dating from 1783 to 1994. The majority of the items are the product of institutions – i.e. businesses, churches, municipal services - though there are a few booklets by individuals, and one hand-drawn family tree. Topics range from advertisements to invitations to fundraising balls to a treatise on human perfectibility. This is a varied collection of disparate materials which were previously part of the Brooklyn Historical Society vertical files.
